news.title: Three or four months needed to raze illegal buildings: Bengaluru civic body
news.para: According to officials, the Palike should follow provisions of Karnataka Town and Country Planning Act while taking action against such buildings, and that procedure will take at least 3 to 4 months.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP urges action against illegal construction in Palam Vihar
news.para: The Palam Vihar C-2 Block RWA and residents have submitted a petition to the high court seeking curbs on illegal construction. The district town planner has registered several FIRs against property owners and requested resealing of unlawfully opened buildings.

news.title: Manoj Bajpayee’s Almora property under investigation for land law violations
news.para: Almora DM Alok Kumar Pandey confirmed that investigations are underway into Bajpayee's acquisition and several similar cases. "Our probe into cases of land law violations has intensified, and action has already been taken in several instances," Pandey said.

news.title: Haryana: 2,100 applications still not cleared under Mukhyamantri Shehri Nikay Swamitva scheme
news.para: "We have 102 applications pending in Gurgaon, and we are expeditiously working to clear the backlog. Out of 705 applications that we have received, 418 were approved and 185 were rejected. The application portal is no longer accepting new submissions," an MCG official said on Monday.

news.title: Gujarat: I-T search on builders uncovers unaccounted transactions worth Rs 150 crore
news.para: "It is believed that the firms under search made bogus entries to evade tax and took large amounts in cash for property transactions. As several of the evasions were related to GST, the DGGI has been intimated of the details for an independent probe in the case," said sources.

news.title: HDFC Bank to monetise properties inherited during merger
news.para: The assets to be sold include the HDFC House in South Mumbai's Churchgate and residential apartments that were allotted to HDFC's senior officials earlier.

news.title: About 140 societies in Noida & Greater Noida fail to maintain rainwater harvesting norms
news.para: The survey revealed that 140 of the 164 societies had non-functioning rainwater harvesting systems, while 10 societies lacked any such facilities. A mere 14 societies were found to have operational rainwater harvesting systems.

news.title: Petition against service provider before Karnataka RERA not maintainable: HC
news.para: Karnataka high court made this observation while allowing a petition filed by M/s Columbia Pacific Communities Pvt Ltd. Bengaluru.

news.title: Kamdhenu Ventures' net profit dips 65.20% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Kamdhenu Ventures' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 54.97 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 16.64 per cent from Rs 65.94 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Macrotech Developers buys 2.8 acres in Pune's Hinjewadi from Paranjape Schemes
news.para: The land parcel was mortgaged by Paranjape Realty Spaces, a group entity of the seller, to avail a loan from ASK Real Estate Special Opportunities Fund II and III managed by ASK Properties Investment Advisors.

news.title: Gurugram: M3M Soulitude buyers accuse builder of unethical practices
news.para: The investors, predominantly from middle-income households, participated in a 10:90 payment scheme in Nov 2021, anticipating handover of their dream homes. Currently, they assert that M3M has not fulfilled its contractual obligations as the project approaches completion.

news.title: Ambuja Cements seeks CCI nod to acquire majority stake in Orient Cement
news.para: ​According to a CCI notice, the proposed transaction is a two-stage acquisition process, initiated through two share purchase agreements (SPAs) on October 22, 2024, will see Ambuja Cements initially acquiring a 46.80 per cent stake in Orient Cement.

news.title: Bhutani Infra acquires Logix City Center in Noida for around Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: "We have acquired Logix City Center from PAG and Logix group promoters. The total investment will be Rs 1,000 crore, including the acquisition cost and renovations," Bhutani Infra CEO Ashish Bhutani told PTI.

news.title: The Ramco Cements' net profit dips 64.21% in Q2 FY25
news.para: The Ramco Cements' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,053.94 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 12.68 per cent from Rs 2,352.09 crore it reported in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Awfis Space Solutions posts net profit of Rs 38.67 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Awfis Space Solutions' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 301.95 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 40.31 per cent from Rs 215.20 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Shree Cement posts net profit of Rs 76.64 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Shree Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 4,235.55 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 13.66 per cent from Rs 4,905.62 crore it reported in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Brick kilns in Punjab contaminate water with toxic metals: Study
news.para: As per the study, these kilns are major sources of heavy metal pollution, largely due to the burning of coal and other fuels in brick production. The findings underscore an urgent need for stricter regulations, including promoting biomass as a cleaner alternative to the vast amounts of coal.

news.title: MPIDC to invest over Rs 200 crore in three industrial zones in Mandsaur
news.para: New industrial zones Maksi, Shajapur and Jaggakhedi in Mandsaur district are slated to be developed in FY 2025.

news.title: Commercial property prices in Germany drop 4.7% in Q3 2024
news.para: It was the second consecutive quarter-on-quarter rise but it is still too early to sound the all-clear, VDP said. Prices may move sideways in the coming quarters, and further setbacks are possible given a weak economy and geopolitical risks.

news.title: Keystone Realtors posts net profit of Rs 65.55 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Keystone Realtors' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 556.22 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 12.18 per cent from Rs 633.33 crore it reported in the similar quarter last year.
